**No-duplication cross-link structure (ONE source of truth per rule):**
- `checklists.md` is declared an INDEX: "Each step links to its authoritative
  section/command; rationale lives there, not here." No lens definitions, no
  contract bodies, no audit-check descriptions are copied in.
- Each of the 3 long docs gets a single pointer line at the top of its relevant
  section: README "Session Boot" -> checklists.md#session-boot;
  review-gate-runbook Purpose -> checklists.md#gate-execution; capture-protocol
  "At bead close" -> checklists.md#close. Bidirectional links so each is
  discoverable from the other.
- Add checklists.md to the README doc index list (README.md:27-53) so it is
  listed alongside the other dogfood docs.
- Drift control: checklist steps point at SECTION ANCHORS, and mechanized rules
  point at the COMMAND name (the script/make target is the source of truth, not a
  prose restatement) — so the only thing that can rot is a link, which surfaces
  as a dead anchor rather than a silently-stale duplicate rule.

