**Risks:**
- Bloat / re-thickening — the goal is LESS load, so checklists.md must stay an
  index of commands+links (target: each flow ~6-8 short lines, no rationale).
  Mitigation: explicit "index, not reference" preamble; the Docs/Reality lens on
  its own acceptance checks it stayed compact.
- Cross-link drift — anchors could rot if a section is later renamed. Mitigation:
  point mechanized steps at COMMAND names (stable) and prose steps at section
  anchors; a dead anchor is visibly broken, unlike a silently-stale copy.
- Duplication temptation — easy to "just paste" the lenses or the close contract.
  Hard rule in the plan: reference 8hq.6's section + the script, never copy.

